		<li id="comment-4268">
			<cite>Diana</cite> Says:
						<br />

			<small class="commentmetadata"><a href="#comment-4268" title="">March 19, 2008 at 9:13 am</a> </small>

			<p>To find this dress, and not need any alterations, is amazing.  A true wonder.  </p>
<p>Funny that this dress didn&#8217;t have a stomacher, that was so common to the times.  A stomacher also allowed some flexibility in changing the look of the bodice, which was so important in those times.  Many woman owned about a handful of dresses, and being able to change bit and pieces of the outfits to make them look new or different was important of the times. </p>
<p>My absolute favorite thing about this dress is the sack back.  I love those backings on dresses.  I think they can appear so regal and gorgeous.</p>

		</li>

	
	
